y low abundances of Sr and Ba support the prospect that both\nmain and weak r-process may have operated during the early phase of Galactic\nchemical evolution. The distribution of [C/N] shows that there are two groups\nof carbon-normal giants with different degrees of mixing. However, it is\ndifficult to explain the observed behavior of the [C/N] of the\nnitrogen-enhanced unevolved stars based on current data.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 13 Jan 2015 16:25:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-01-14"}
