{"id":"1501.03147","submitter":"Aaron Kelly","authors":"Aaron Kelly, Nora Brackbill, Thomas E. Markland","title":"Accurate nonadiabatic quantum dynamics on the cheap: making the most of\n  mean field theory with master equations","comments":"10 pages, 6 figures","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1063/1.4913686","report-no":null,"categories":"physics.chem-ph cond-mat.stat-mech","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  In this article we show how Ehrenfest mean field theory can be made both a\nmore accurate and efficient method to treat nonadiabatic quantum dynamics by\ncombining it with the generalized quantum master equation framework. The\nresulting mean field generalized quantum master equation (MF-GQME) approach is\na non-perturbative and non-Markovian theory to treat open quantum systems\nwithout any restrictions on the form of the Hamiltonian that it can be applied\nto. By studying relaxation dynamics in a wide range of dynamical regimes,\ntypical of charge and energy transfer, we show that MF-GQME provides a much\nhigher accuracy than a direct application of mean field theory. In addition,\nthese increases in accuracy are accompanied by computational speed-ups of\nbetween one and two orders of magnitude that become larger as the system\nbecomes more nonadiabatic. This combination of quantum-classical theory and\nmaster equation techniques thus makes it possible to obtain the accuracy of\nmuch more computationally expensive approaches at a cost lower than even mean\nfield dynamics, providing the ability to treat the quantum dynamics of\natomistic condensed phase systems for long times.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 13 Jan 2015 20:57:42 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 17 Feb 2015 02:43:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-23"}
